738
00:50:20,235 --> 00:50:21,796
Scratch that. Say whatever you like.

739
00:50:21,876 --> 00:50:24,556
Shake hands with
Sears Braithwaite of Bullard.

740
00:50:24,876 --> 00:50:26,435
Glad to know you, Barnes.

741
00:50:26,796 --> 00:50:28,516
This is Zebulon Cardozo...

742
00:50:28,596 --> 00:50:31,597
...one of Hudsucker's largest
and most loyal stockholders.

743
00:50:31,677 --> 00:50:33,998
What's this I hear
about you being an imbecile?

744
00:50:34,078 --> 00:50:35,638
What's ailing you, boy?

745
00:50:35,798 --> 00:50:39,759
Last week, my stock was worth twice
what it is now. I think I'll sell...

746
00:50:39,839 --> 00:50:43,719
...the whole kit and caboodle, boy,
unless I see a vast improvement.

747
00:50:44,079 --> 00:50:46,560
What you've got here, son, is a range war!

748
00:50:46,720 --> 00:50:50,440
You gonna have to circle our wagons
or I'm gonna get out of your wagon train.

749
00:50:51,961 --> 00:50:54,042
No need for concern, sir.
It's only natural...

750
00:50:54,162 --> 00:50:57,242
...in a period of transition for the more
timid elements to run for cover.

751
00:50:57,282 --> 00:51:00,202
Yellow? I'll show you yellow, boy!

752
00:51:00,922 --> 00:51:03,803
You mind now and quit acting
like such an old grizzly.

753
00:51:04,003 --> 00:51:05,803
Step lively here, Norville.

754
00:51:06,324 --> 00:51:09,405
I'm sorry, I thought maybe if I showed him
the long view...

755
00:51:09,645 --> 00:51:12,324
And this is Thorstensen Finlandson...

756
00:51:12,564 --> 00:51:15,204
...who heads a radical, splinter group
of disgruntled investors.

757
00:51:15,284 --> 00:51:16,645
Pleased to meet you.

758
00:51:16,725 --> 00:51:20,125
It might interest you to know I studied
a little Finnish in high school.

759
00:51:20,165 --> 00:51:21,766
I hope I'm not too rusty.

760
00:51:29,206 --> 00:51:32,607
Ladies and gentlemen, distinguished
members of the Hudsucker Board...

761
00:51:32,647 --> 00:51:36,728
...I give you the Rajah of Romance,
the Ministereo of Moonlight...

762
00:51:37,088 --> 00:51:39,368
...the incredible, the unforgettable...

763
00:51:39,448 --> 00:51:42,248
...Mr. Vic Tenetta!

764
00:51:48,730 --> 00:51:50,370
"Rajah". I like that.

765
00:52:31,697 --> 00:52:33,057
What happened?

766
00:52:34,417 --> 00:52:38,738
Nothing. Just the more timid investors
are no longer running for cover.

767
00:52:38,898 --> 00:52:39,978
Let me look.

768
00:52:40,578 --> 00:52:41,899
Sid found me the ice pack.

769
00:52:41,939 --> 00:52:44,539
Let me hold it or you'll have a real shiner.

770
00:52:45,899 --> 00:52:48,540
I guess people are pretty hot
over this imbecile story.

771
00:52:49,140 --> 00:52:50,420
I'm sorry.

772
00:52:51,100 --> 00:52:54,901
It's not your fault. You've the one person
standing by me through all this.

773
00:52:54,981 --> 00:52:57,661
Norville, there's something
I have to tell you.

774
00:52:58,581 --> 00:52:59,622
You see...

775
00:53:00,262 --> 00:53:02,142
...I'm not really a secretary.

776
00:53:03,062 --> 00:53:04,182
I know that, Amy.

777
00:53:04,262 --> 00:53:05,223
You do?

778
00:53:05,423 --> 00:53:08,424
I understand you're not very skilled yet
in the secretarial arts...

779
00:53:08,504 --> 00:53:11,505
...but I'll tell you a secret:
I'm not that skilled as president.

780
00:53:11,545 --> 00:53:14,864
-I know I put up a big front, but...
-I believe in you, Norville.

781
00:53:16,464 --> 00:53:17,505
At least...

782
00:53:18,025 --> 00:53:20,345
...I believe in your intentions.

783
00:53:20,585 --> 00:53:23,906
I don't blame them, really.
I suppose I have made a mess of things.

784
00:53:24,506 --> 00:53:26,706
Those folks have to protect
their investment.

785
00:53:26,746 --> 00:53:28,305
Most of them are very nice people.

786
00:53:28,345 --> 00:53:31,666
Listen, you can't trust people here
like you did in Muncie.

787
00:53:31,706 --> 00:53:33,707
Certain people are...

788
00:53:33,787 --> 00:53:37,588
Did you ever go to the top of Larson's
feed tower and look out over the town?

789
00:53:38,508 --> 00:53:39,828
On Farm Route 17?

790
00:53:40,188 --> 00:53:42,549
Oh, yes, in Muncie.

791
00:53:43,708 --> 00:53:46,269
No, Vidalia. Farm Route 17.

792
00:53:47,910 --> 00:53:51,190
Seventeen. Yes, I....
Well, no, no. I never really...

793
00:53:52,910 --> 00:53:56,511
The guys from the Varsity Squad
would bring their dates up there...

794
00:53:57,552 --> 00:53:58,831
...to hold hands.

795
00:53:59,631 --> 00:54:01,792
Of course, I never made Varsity.

796
00:54:04,352 --> 00:54:06,113
There's a place I go now.

797
00:54:06,913 --> 00:54:09,834
Cutest little place near my apartment
in Greenwich Village.

798
00:54:09,914 --> 00:54:11,794
It's called "Ann's 440".

799
00:54:12,115 --> 00:54:13,475
It's a beatnik bar.

800
00:54:13,555 --> 00:54:14,914
-You don't say?
-Yes.

801
00:54:14,994 --> 00:54:15,954
A beatnik bar.

802
00:54:16,034 --> 00:54:19,395
You can get carrot juice or ltalian coffee
and the people there...

803
00:54:19,995 --> 00:54:21,635
Well, none of them quite fit in.

804
00:54:22,235 --> 00:54:23,395
You'd love it.

805
00:54:23,875 --> 00:54:25,276
Come there with me.

806
00:54:25,756 --> 00:54:28,516
There's a marathon poetry-reading
on New Year's Eve. I go every year.

807
00:54:28,556 --> 00:54:30,756
-It's marvelous!
-Every year?

808
00:54:32,836 --> 00:54:37,078
Well, this year, if it's good,
I plan to make it a tradition.

809
00:54:39,238 --> 00:54:41,118
My, it certainly is beautiful.

810
00:54:41,878 --> 00:54:43,359
The people...

811
00:54:43,799 --> 00:54:45,278
...look like ants.

812
00:54:46,399 --> 00:54:49,440
The Hindus, and the beatniks also,
say that...

813
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:52,640
...in our next lives some of us
will come back as ants.

814
00:54:53,080 --> 00:54:57,081
Some will be butterflies, others will be
elephants or creatures of the sea.

815
00:54:57,241 --> 00:54:58,642
What a beautiful thought.

816
00:54:58,802 --> 00:55:01,402
What do you think you were
in a previous life?

817
00:55:02,442 --> 00:55:04,002
Oh, I don't know.

818
00:55:04,762 --> 00:55:06,202
Maybe I was just...

819
00:55:06,602 --> 00:55:10,564
...a fast-talking career gal
who thought she was one of the boys.

820
00:55:10,684 --> 00:55:11,804
Oh, no, Amy.

821
00:55:12,044 --> 00:55:14,804
Pardon me for saying so,
but I find that very far-fetched.

822
00:55:14,924 --> 00:55:18,764
-There really is something I must tell you.
-That person would come back as a hog.

823
00:55:18,844 --> 00:55:21,445
I find it more likely that you were...

824
00:55:22,765 --> 00:55:23,765
...a gazelle...

825
00:55:24,685 --> 00:55:28,166
...with long, graceful legs,
gamboling through the underbrush.

826
00:55:29,006 --> 00:55:30,565
Perhaps we met once.

827
00:55:31,245 --> 00:55:33,846
A chance encounter in a forest glade.

828
00:55:35,727 --> 00:55:38,168
I must have been an antelope or an ibex.

829
00:55:39,328 --> 00:55:42,728
The times we must've had
foraging together for sustenance...

830
00:55:43,649 --> 00:55:46,128
...snorfling water
from a mountain stream...

831
00:55:46,689 --> 00:55:50,130
...picking the grubs and burrs
from one another's coats.

832
00:55:52,770 --> 00:55:57,131
Or perhaps we simply touched horns
briefly and went our separate ways.

833
00:55:58,411 --> 00:56:00,931
Oh, I wish it were that simple, Norville.

834
00:56:02,292 --> 00:56:06,332
I wish I was still a gazelle
and you were an antelope...

835
00:56:07,172 --> 00:56:08,453
...or an ibex.

836
00:56:12,854 --> 00:56:14,415
Can I at least call you...

837
00:56:14,735 --> 00:56:15,734
...deer?

838
00:56:18,774 --> 00:56:19,854
You're funny.

839
00:56:19,894 --> 00:56:23,055
Seriously, Amy, it's what
your beatnik friends call "karma".

840
00:56:23,255 --> 00:56:24,055
Karma.

841
00:56:24,135 --> 00:56:26,976
The great circle of life, death and rebirth.

842
00:56:27,136 --> 00:56:30,696
I think I heard of that.
What goes around comes around.

843
00:56:30,776 --> 00:56:34,176
That's it. A great wheel
that gives us all what we deserve.

844
00:56:35,497 --> 00:56:38,578
I've go to show Sid and all the guys
I deserve their confidence.

845
00:56:38,658 --> 00:56:41,018
Tomorrow's my big presentation
to the board.

846
00:56:43,418 --> 00:56:44,619
Kiss me, Amy!

847
00:56:44,979 --> 00:56:46,458
Kiss me once for luck.

848
00:56:47,819 --> 00:56:49,019
Sure, Norville.

849
00:57:28,786 --> 00:57:30,106
You know, for kids!

850
00:57:30,386 --> 00:57:34,106
It has economy, simplicity, low
production cost, potential for mass appeal.

851
00:57:34,146 --> 00:57:36,387
All that spells out great profitability.

852
00:57:36,427 --> 00:57:39,067
I had the boys at R&D
make this prototype...

853
00:57:39,107 --> 00:57:41,028
...so our discussion
could have some focus...

854
00:57:41,068 --> 00:57:44,828
...and to give you gentleman a firsthand
look at how exciting this gizmo is.

855
00:57:44,868 --> 00:57:48,148
It's fun, healthy, good exercise,
and the kids'll love it.

856
00:57:48,268 --> 00:57:51,229
We put a little sand inside
to make the experience more pleasant.

857
00:57:51,269 --> 00:57:54,470
The great part is we don't have
to charge an arm and a leg.

858
00:57:57,030 --> 00:57:59,751
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Does it have rules?

859
00:57:59,831 --> 00:58:01,912
-Can more than one play?
-Why is it a game?

860
00:58:01,992 --> 00:58:03,511
-Is it a game?
-Will it break?

861
00:58:03,591 --> 00:58:05,672
-It better break eventually.
-Is there an object?

862
00:58:05,752 --> 00:58:08,312
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Does it have batteries?

863
00:58:08,392 --> 00:58:11,113
-Could we charge extra for them?
-Is it safe for toddlers?

864
00:58:11,193 --> 00:58:13,514
-How do you know you're finished?
-How does it stop?

865
00:58:13,554 --> 00:58:16,075
-Is that a boy's model?
-Can a parent assemble it?

866
00:58:16,195 --> 00:58:20,234
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Is there a larger model for the obese?

867
00:58:20,314 --> 00:58:22,435
What the hell is it?

868
00:58:22,475 --> 00:58:23,755
Well, it's....

869
00:58:27,435 --> 00:58:28,476
Brilliant!

870
00:58:30,316 --> 00:58:31,356
Genius.

871
00:58:32,396 --> 00:58:35,756
It's exactly what Hudsucker Industry needs
at this juncture.

872
00:58:36,636 --> 00:58:40,918
Even a blind man can tell you
there'll be an enormous demand for this...

873
00:58:42,318 --> 00:58:43,358
...this....

874
00:58:44,238 --> 00:58:45,238
Congratulations.

875
00:58:45,318 --> 00:58:47,719
You've outdone yourself.
You've reinvented the wheel.

876
00:58:47,799 --> 00:58:50,639
I'll recommend to the board
that we proceed immediately...

877
00:58:52,279 --> 00:58:53,600
...and that the...

878
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:57,880
...dingus be mass-produced
with all deliberate speed.

879
00:58:58,280 --> 00:58:59,961
Although, you realize...

880
00:59:00,401 --> 00:59:01,641
...of course...

881
00:59:04,721 --> 00:59:06,002
...as president...

882
00:59:06,322 --> 00:59:08,242
...the ultimate decision is yours.

883
00:59:09,402 --> 00:59:10,602
I'm for it.

884
00:59:57,370 --> 00:59:58,650
The Flying Doughnut!

885
00:59:58,690 --> 01:00:00,971
-The Dancing Dingus!
-The Belly-Go-Round.

886
01:00:01,051 --> 01:00:02,251
The Swingerina!

887
01:00:02,331 --> 01:00:03,732
The Wacky Circumference!

888
01:00:03,772 --> 01:00:05,531
Uncle Midriff!

889
01:00:35,095 --> 01:00:36,816
-We need something short!
-Sharp!

890
01:00:36,896 --> 01:00:37,576
Snappy!

891
01:00:37,656 --> 01:00:40,017
-With a little jazz!
-The Shazzammeter!

892
01:00:40,097 --> 01:00:42,217
-The Hipster!
-The Daddy-O!

893
01:01:21,824 --> 01:01:23,424
-The Hoopsucker.
-The Hudswinger.

894
01:01:23,504 --> 01:01:25,665
-The Hoopsucker!
-The Hudswinger!

895
01:01:25,705 --> 01:01:27,385
-The Hoopsucker!
-The Hudswinger!

896
01:01:54,349 --> 01:01:56,390
-Fellas!
-You got something?

897
01:01:58,030 --> 01:01:59,750
I got something!

898
01:05:04,020 --> 01:05:08,022
Rockwell News presents: Tidbits of Time.

899
01:05:08,382 --> 01:05:10,982
World news in pictures, we kid you not!

900
01:05:11,342 --> 01:05:14,462
As Old Man 1958 hobbles
towards his finish...

901
01:05:15,022 --> 01:05:17,343
...Barnes is the name
on every American lip.

902
01:05:17,503 --> 01:05:20,904
Norville Barnes, young president
of Hudsucker Industries...

903
01:05:20,944 --> 01:05:24,464
...a boy bred in the heartland,
but now the toast of New York.

904
01:05:24,944 --> 01:05:29,265
Barnes is the brainy inventor of America's
craziest craze: The Hula Hoop!

905
01:05:29,785 --> 01:05:33,345
Reaping huge profits for his company
and winning the hearts...

906
01:05:33,625 --> 01:05:36,066
...and hips of every youngster in America!

907
01:05:37,466 --> 01:05:38,866
Did I say youngster?

908
01:05:39,106 --> 01:05:41,986
Here's Mom taking a break
from her household chores...

909
01:05:42,706 --> 01:05:45,067
...and even Dad is swinging into the act!

910
01:05:46,627 --> 01:05:51,228
Cards, letters, congratulations come
pouring in from Kankakee to Petaluma...

911
01:05:51,588 --> 01:05:54,669
...including one very special
long-distance call.

912
01:05:54,908 --> 01:05:56,789
He's on! He's on the line!

913
01:06:03,190 --> 01:06:05,390
Hello, Norville. This is the President.

914
01:06:05,831 --> 01:06:09,192
I just wanted to congratulate you.
I'm very proud of you.

915
01:06:09,792 --> 01:06:12,072
Mrs. Eisenhower is very proud of you.

916
01:06:12,432 --> 01:06:14,872
The American people are very proud of you.

917
01:06:21,674 --> 01:06:24,555
How'd you come up with the idea
for the Hula Hoop?

918
01:06:24,915 --> 01:06:26,754
It was no great idea, really.

919
01:06:26,874 --> 01:06:30,475
A thing like this takes a whole company
to put together. I'm grateful.

920
01:06:30,755 --> 01:06:33,555
Did you have any idea
there'd be such a huge response?

921
01:06:33,595 --> 01:06:36,596
Frankly, I don't think anybody
expected this much hoopla.

922
01:06:38,396 --> 01:06:41,715
"Hoopla on the Hula Hoop".
Can we quote you on that, Mr. Barnes?

923
01:06:41,835 --> 01:06:43,196
Sure, I guess.

924
01:06:43,876 --> 01:06:46,157
Will you give yourself a nice, fat raise?

925
01:06:47,357 --> 01:06:48,518
Come on, you guys.

926
01:06:55,838 --> 01:07:00,400
What scientific principle explains
the motion of this wheel of wonder?

927
01:07:00,480 --> 01:07:02,520
The dingus is quite simple, really.

928
01:07:02,800 --> 01:07:06,801
It operates on the same principles that
keep the earth spinning around the sun...

929
01:07:06,881 --> 01:07:11,161
...and that keeps you from flying off
the earth into the cold reaches of space...

930
01:07:11,281 --> 01:07:13,722
...where you would die
like a miserable Schwein.

931
01:07:13,762 --> 01:07:15,802
Yes, the principle is the same...

932
01:07:16,242 --> 01:07:20,283
...except for the piece of grit
they put in to make the experience...

933
01:07:21,003 --> 01:07:22,124
...more pleasant.

934
01:07:22,204 --> 01:07:24,805
Yes, it's hula-hula everywhere!

935
01:07:24,885 --> 01:07:27,524
From the parties of the Park Avenue
smart set...

936
01:07:30,564 --> 01:07:34,085
...to sweethearts who want
to be married in the swing of things.

937
01:07:38,286 --> 01:07:41,525
Did the board consider you an "Idea Man"
when they promoted you?

938
01:07:41,605 --> 01:07:45,006
I guess. I don't think they promoted me
because they thought I was a schmo.

939
01:07:45,086 --> 01:07:48,247
What's the next big idea for you
and Hudsucker Industries?

940
01:07:48,327 --> 01:07:51,568
I don't know. An idea like this sweet baby
doesn't just come overnight.

941
01:07:51,648 --> 01:07:55,729
Although, I'll tell you one thing:
I certainly didn't expect all this hoopla.

942
01:07:56,489 --> 01:07:58,008
You can quote me on that.

943
01:08:05,330 --> 01:08:08,411
Rumpus Magazine has called you
the most eligible bachelor of the year.

944
01:08:08,491 --> 01:08:11,492
And society pages have been linking you
with fashion model Za-Za.

945
01:08:11,532 --> 01:08:15,412
There's no truth to the rumors.
We're just dear friends. Isn't that right?

946
01:08:22,293 --> 01:08:26,375
How do you respond to the charges that
you're out of ideas? Have you run dry?

947
01:08:26,535 --> 01:08:30,334
Not at all. Just this week I came up
with several new sweet ideas.

948
01:08:30,694 --> 01:08:34,935
A larger model Hula Hoop for the portly,
a battery option for the lazy or spastic.

949
01:08:35,055 --> 01:08:37,335
A model with extra sand
for the hard-of-hearing.

950
01:08:37,415 --> 01:08:39,016
I'm earning my keep.

951
01:08:39,056 --> 01:08:41,616
Speaking of that,
do you expect to get a raise?

952
01:08:41,936 --> 01:08:45,816
By anyone's account I single-handedly
have saved Hudsucker Industries.

953
01:08:45,936 --> 01:08:50,338
Our stock is worth more now than ever.
Yes, I expect to be compensated for that.

954
01:09:09,421 --> 01:09:11,141
Pull yourself together, man.

955
01:09:11,221 --> 01:09:12,622
Nobody told me!

956
01:09:13,541 --> 01:09:15,702
You sold all our stock?

957
01:09:16,142 --> 01:09:17,662
We dumped the whole load.

958
01:09:17,742 --> 01:09:20,022
I had 20,000 shares!

959
01:09:20,703 --> 01:09:22,343
I'd be a millionaire now!

960
01:09:22,423 --> 01:09:24,424
Sure. We'd all be millionaires.

961
01:09:25,104 --> 01:09:27,105
There's no point in looking back.

962
01:09:27,825 --> 01:09:31,584
At the time, Stillson thought that dumping
our position would panic the market...

963
01:09:31,664 --> 01:09:33,585
...further depress the stock.

964
01:09:33,825 --> 01:09:37,225
Then we could buy it back and more,
of course, once it got cheap.

965
01:09:37,305 --> 01:09:38,225
Cheap?

966
01:09:38,625 --> 01:09:40,466
It's never been more valuable!

967
01:09:42,306 --> 01:09:43,505
And I'm ruined.

968
01:09:44,225 --> 01:09:45,186
Ruined!

969
01:09:52,188 --> 01:09:55,268
I'm getting off this merry-go-round!

970
01:10:04,990 --> 01:10:06,070
Plexiglass.

971
01:10:06,630 --> 01:10:08,310
Had it installed last week.

972
01:10:21,673 --> 01:10:23,313
So, the kid caught a wave.

973
01:10:24,954 --> 01:10:28,315
Right now, he and his dingus are on top.

974
01:10:28,875 --> 01:10:30,554
Well, this too shall pass.

975
01:10:31,434 --> 01:10:34,435
Myrtle J. Mussburger
did not raise her boy to go...

976
01:10:34,955 --> 01:10:37,595
...knock-kneed at the first sign of adversity.

977
01:10:37,635 --> 01:10:40,436
I say, we made this chump,
we can break him!

978
01:10:41,276 --> 01:10:43,956
I say, the higher he climbs,
the harder he drops!

979
01:10:45,755 --> 01:10:46,796
I say, yes...

980
01:10:47,676 --> 01:10:49,277
...the kid has a future...

981
01:10:50,637 --> 01:10:51,837
...and in it...

982
01:10:52,798 --> 01:10:54,718
...I see shame, dishonor...

983
01:10:55,358 --> 01:10:57,078
...ignominy, disgrace.

984
01:11:00,878 --> 01:11:03,039
The music plays, the wheel turns...

985
01:11:04,240 --> 01:11:06,200
...and our spin ain't over yet.

986
01:11:29,925 --> 01:11:31,844
For Pete's sakes, Norville!

987
01:11:32,204 --> 01:11:34,004
Where have you been hiding?

988
01:11:34,164 --> 01:11:37,365
Do you know what those nincompoops
in the boardroom are doing?

989
01:11:37,445 --> 01:11:39,005
I wouldn't call them nincompoops.

990
01:11:39,085 --> 01:11:41,446
They're going to discharge 8%
of the workforce here!

991
01:11:41,526 --> 01:11:44,366
In New York City alone,
that means 1,800 people out of work!

992
01:11:44,446 --> 01:11:46,765
People with wives, children and families!

993
01:11:47,046 --> 01:11:49,126
We're pruning away some of the dead wood.

994
01:11:49,206 --> 01:11:51,207
You mean you know about this?

995
01:11:51,247 --> 01:11:52,767
Know about it? Sure.

996
01:11:52,847 --> 01:11:55,848
You think the board would do anything
without my authorization?

997
01:11:55,928 --> 01:11:57,328
It was my idea.

998
01:11:57,408 --> 01:11:58,688
-Your...
-Sure it was.

999
01:11:58,768 --> 01:12:01,568
We're in a period of transition.
Things have slowed down.

1000
01:12:01,648 --> 01:12:04,329
You're being awfully kind to yourself,
Norville Barnes.

1001
01:12:04,369 --> 01:12:07,690
You've slowed down, sitting up here
not doing a lick of work.

1002
01:12:08,210 --> 01:12:12,891
You haven't come up with an idea since
the Hoop and the reason is plain to see!

1003
01:12:12,971 --> 01:12:15,372
You've forgotten what made your ideas
exciting to you.

1004
01:12:15,452 --> 01:12:17,732
It wasn't for the fame and wealth....

1005
01:12:17,812 --> 01:12:21,492
Would you get out of here?
You too, sisters, move it. Out!

1006
01:12:23,653 --> 01:12:26,694
I've been watching you, even though
you've been trying to avoid me.

1007
01:12:26,854 --> 01:12:27,534
Shut up!

1008
01:12:27,574 --> 01:12:29,815
Don't think I haven't noticed
how you've changed.

1009
01:12:29,855 --> 01:12:31,574
I used to think you were a swell guy.

1010
01:12:31,654 --> 01:12:33,614
To be honest,
I thought you were an imbecile.

1011
01:12:34,014 --> 01:12:34,774
Shut up!

1012
01:12:34,854 --> 01:12:38,295
Then I figured out you were a swell guy.
A little slow maybe, but a swell guy.

1013
01:12:38,375 --> 01:12:41,695
Maybe you're not so slow
but you're not so swell either.

1014
01:12:41,776 --> 01:12:43,896
Looks like you're an imbecile, after all.
Shut up!

1015
01:12:44,576 --> 01:12:47,896
You haven't talked to me for a week
and now I'm going to say my piece.

1016
01:12:47,936 --> 01:12:49,896
Look, I've never been...

1017
01:12:50,816 --> 01:12:53,297
...dumped by a fella before,
and that hurts...

1018
01:12:53,657 --> 01:12:56,418
...but what really hurts is watching you
out-run your soul!

1019
01:12:56,498 --> 01:12:58,778
Chasing after money and ease
and the respect of a board...

1020
01:12:58,858 --> 01:13:01,139
...that wouldn't give you the time of day...

1021
01:13:01,179 --> 01:13:02,138
...if you....

1022
01:13:02,698 --> 01:13:04,059
Worked in a watch factory?

1023
01:13:05,539 --> 01:13:06,860
Shut up! Exactly.

1024
01:13:08,060 --> 01:13:11,460
Norville, don't you remember
how you used to feel about the Hoop?

1025
01:13:12,020 --> 01:13:15,462
You told me you'd bring a smile
to the hips of everyone in America...

1026
01:13:15,542 --> 01:13:17,421
...regardless of race, creed or color.

1027
01:13:17,501 --> 01:13:20,982
Finally, there'd be a thingamajig
that would bring everyone together...

1028
01:13:21,022 --> 01:13:23,262
...even if it kept them apart spatially.

1029
01:13:23,702 --> 01:13:24,743
"You know...

1030
01:13:25,223 --> 01:13:26,223
"...for kids".

1031
01:13:27,063 --> 01:13:28,024
Your words...

1032
01:13:29,064 --> 01:13:30,144
...not mine.

1033
01:13:31,465 --> 01:13:33,064
I used to love Norville Barnes.

1034
01:13:34,104 --> 01:13:35,424
Yes, love him...

1035
01:13:36,104 --> 01:13:39,985
...when he was just a swell kid
with hot ideas who was in over his head.

1036
01:13:40,705 --> 01:13:42,906
Now your head's too big to be in over!

1037
01:13:43,026 --> 01:13:44,866
Consider this my resignation.

1038
01:13:46,106 --> 01:13:47,505
Effective immediately!

1039
01:15:04,278 --> 01:15:05,999
Buddy, buddy.

1040
01:15:06,879 --> 01:15:07,879
Buddy.

1041
01:15:08,760 --> 01:15:10,040
Oh, buddy.

1042
01:15:19,441 --> 01:15:20,722
Buddy. You busy?

1043
01:15:22,482 --> 01:15:25,802
Looks like you nodded off there, buddy.
Say, you got a minute?

1044
01:15:29,243 --> 01:15:30,564
Is this important?

1045
01:15:30,644 --> 01:15:33,805
I think so. It's this little idea
I've been working on.

1046
01:15:33,845 --> 01:15:36,444
You see, I don't intend
to be an elevator boy forever.

1047
01:15:36,524 --> 01:15:38,044
Take a look at this sweet baby!

1048
01:15:38,124 --> 01:15:40,445
Get it? Incredibly convenient, isn't it?

1049
01:15:40,565 --> 01:15:42,045
You know, for drinks?

1050
01:15:42,245 --> 01:15:46,046
This is how it works. It's got these ridges
on the side that give it its whammy.

1051
01:15:46,166 --> 01:15:49,645
You don't have to drink like this.
You can drink like this.

1052
01:15:49,765 --> 01:15:51,966
I call it the "Buzz-Sucker".
You get it, buddy?

1053
01:15:52,046 --> 01:15:55,767
People are dying for this and
we won't have to charge an arm and a leg.

1054
01:15:55,807 --> 01:15:57,008
Wait a minute.

1055
01:16:11,730 --> 01:16:12,690
This...

1056
01:16:15,651 --> 01:16:16,771
...is worthless!

1057
01:16:17,051 --> 01:16:18,131
But, buddy!

1058
01:16:18,452 --> 01:16:21,252
This is the most idiotic thing
I've ever seen in my life.

1059
01:16:21,332 --> 01:16:23,572
Nobody wants a hair-brained product
like this.

1060
01:16:23,612 --> 01:16:24,692
You see, Buzz...

1061
01:16:24,772 --> 01:16:26,772
...it lacks the creative spark...

1062
01:16:27,132 --> 01:16:30,013
...the unalloyed genius
that made something like, say...

1063
01:16:30,814 --> 01:16:32,454
...the Hula Hoop such a success.

1064
01:16:32,534 --> 01:16:34,895
How dare you barge in here
and take up my valuable time!

1065
01:16:34,974 --> 01:16:36,294
I've got a company to run!

1066
01:16:38,534 --> 01:16:41,335
I can't have every deadbeat
on the payroll pestering me...

1067
01:16:41,375 --> 01:16:43,055
...with their idiotic brainwaves.

1068
01:16:43,135 --> 01:16:44,295
I'm sorry, buddy.

1069
01:16:44,375 --> 01:16:45,535
An example must be made!

1070
01:16:46,016 --> 01:16:47,376
What do you mean?

1071
01:16:48,456 --> 01:16:49,576
You're fired!

1072
01:16:50,295 --> 01:16:52,296
Is that plain enough for you?

1073
01:16:57,417 --> 01:16:58,778
Oh, buddy!

1074
01:16:59,498 --> 01:17:01,098
And don't call me "buddy"!

1075
01:17:01,858 --> 01:17:05,738
Oh, please, sir! This job running
the elevator, it's all I got!

1076
01:17:06,178 --> 01:17:08,139
It's okay if you don't like the Buzz-Sucker!

1077
01:17:08,219 --> 01:17:10,900
Just let me keep my job,
I'm praying to you!

1078
01:17:11,740 --> 01:17:13,020
Get out of my office!

1079
01:17:13,500 --> 01:17:14,740
Get up! Up!

1080
01:17:15,820 --> 01:17:18,301
We don't crawl here
at Hudsucker Industries!

1081
01:17:19,902 --> 01:17:21,141
I'm sorry, sir!

1082
01:17:21,301 --> 01:17:22,422
I'm sorry!

1083
01:17:36,304 --> 01:17:37,704
Thank you, Aloysius.

1084
01:17:42,625 --> 01:17:43,745
This is...

1085
01:17:45,505 --> 01:17:46,465
...useful.

1086
01:18:03,868 --> 01:18:07,949
I'm sorry I'm late, Sid. That back nine
at Riverdale's really murder.

1087
01:18:09,189 --> 01:18:11,950
It's a tough course. A real lollapalooza.

1088
01:18:13,430 --> 01:18:14,630
Sit down, son.

1089
01:18:17,871 --> 01:18:21,791
I thought the boardroom would be
a swell place to chat undisturbed.

1090
01:18:22,871 --> 01:18:26,112
Seems we've got some security problems
here at the Hud.

1091
01:18:27,192 --> 01:18:28,072
You don't say.

1092
01:18:28,112 --> 01:18:32,274
Ordinarily, I wouldn't bother you with it,
but this is embarrassing.

1093
01:18:33,594 --> 01:18:35,675
It concerns you directly.

1094
01:18:35,995 --> 01:18:38,474
-How's that?
-It's not serious in itself.

1095
01:18:39,114 --> 01:18:41,755
Some elevator boy that you'd fired
came to me...

1096
01:18:42,355 --> 01:18:45,995
...claiming that you'd stolen
the idea for the dingus.

1097
01:18:46,315 --> 01:18:47,916
You'd stolen it from him.

1098
01:18:50,956 --> 01:18:53,275
-Maybe I was a little rough on him...
-Forget it.

1099
01:18:53,355 --> 01:18:56,837
You don't have to explain to me.
He's a little person. He's nothing.

1100
01:18:56,917 --> 01:18:58,397
Fire whoever you want.

1101
01:19:00,318 --> 01:19:02,038
No, the problem is...

1102
01:19:02,678 --> 01:19:03,958
...who you hired.

1103
01:19:04,398 --> 01:19:05,438
That dame.

1104
01:19:05,879 --> 01:19:07,398
A spy, as it turns out.

1105
01:19:08,278 --> 01:19:10,959
She must have gotten
to that elevator schnook...

1106
01:19:11,679 --> 01:19:13,720
...and her paper is going to town.

1107
01:19:14,800 --> 01:19:19,001
Sure, sure, we tried to kill the story,
but the Argus won't play ball.

1108
01:19:20,801 --> 01:19:23,841
The problem the board will have is
you hired this woman...

1109
01:19:24,202 --> 01:19:25,842
...and you kept her on...

1110
01:19:26,162 --> 01:19:28,562
...while she was making
a chump out of you.

1111
01:19:29,122 --> 01:19:30,803
Serious error in judgement.

1112
01:19:32,323 --> 01:19:33,804
Business is war, kid.

1113
01:19:34,884 --> 01:19:37,285
Take no prisoners, give no second chances.

1114
01:19:40,964 --> 01:19:43,325
When the board meets after New Year's...

1115
01:19:43,485 --> 01:19:44,925
...your position....

1116
01:19:47,525 --> 01:19:49,206
Looks like you're finished.

1117
01:19:49,926 --> 01:19:50,966
Washed up.

1118
01:19:56,486 --> 01:19:58,367
Fourteenth hole at Riverdale...

1119
01:19:58,727 --> 01:20:00,247
...some use a mashie...

1120
01:20:00,447 --> 01:20:01,888
...some use a niblick.

1121
01:20:02,848 --> 01:20:03,848
Niblick.

1122
01:20:04,408 --> 01:20:06,568
You get more loft, more backspin.

1123
01:20:11,289 --> 01:20:12,369
That dame...

1124
01:20:13,770 --> 01:20:16,050
...she got your throat pretty well slit.

1125
01:20:17,130 --> 01:20:19,051
When you're dead, you stay dead.

1126
01:20:19,891 --> 01:20:22,252
You don't believe me,
ask Waring Hudsucker.

1127
01:20:24,451 --> 01:20:25,732
Tough luck, kid.

1128
01:20:26,372 --> 01:20:28,012
You had a short climb up.

1129
01:20:29,092 --> 01:20:30,572
It's a long way down.

1130
01:20:42,774 --> 01:20:46,175
-You can't print that!
-We are! She hits the streets tonight.

1131
01:20:47,135 --> 01:20:48,775
And she's dynamite!

1132
01:20:48,855 --> 01:20:52,816
But it's the bunk! Norville showed me his
design for the whatsit the day I met him.

1133
01:20:52,896 --> 01:20:55,576
Buzz couldn't have invented it.
Look at him, he's an imbecile.

1134
01:20:55,656 --> 01:20:59,417
Aren't you a broken record?
Gunderson did design it. He's a prodigy.

1135
01:20:59,537 --> 01:21:01,898
-Says who?
-You're not the only one with sources.

1136
01:21:01,938 --> 01:21:04,458
Smith has a senior source
on the Hud Board. Very senior.

1137
01:21:04,698 --> 01:21:06,818
I bet his initials are Sidney J. Mussburger.

1138
01:21:07,538 --> 01:21:10,098
You lost it. You gone soft,
by the looks of it.

1139
01:21:10,178 --> 01:21:11,699
Soft on the dummy from Dubuque.

1140
01:21:12,699 --> 01:21:13,980
-Muncie.
-Whatever!

1141
01:21:14,060 --> 01:21:17,780
This story's hot and you're no longer
on top of it. It's the scoop of the century!

1142
01:21:17,860 --> 01:21:19,941
The other papers won't have this
till tomorrow!

1143
01:21:20,021 --> 01:21:23,782
Allemeinisher Zeitung, Le Figaro
will be choking on our dust come morning.

1144
01:21:23,822 --> 01:21:27,142
You're fools, both of you!
You're being used, don't you see?

1145
01:21:27,462 --> 01:21:30,262
Take a break. You worked hard on this.
You broke it for us.

1146
01:21:30,342 --> 01:21:32,663
But it's passed you by
and Smith's taking up the slack.

1147
01:21:34,863 --> 01:21:36,144
You want slack...

1148
01:21:36,744 --> 01:21:38,024
...I'll give you slack!

1149
01:21:38,064 --> 01:21:42,344
You're not putting me out to pasture!
I quit! Consider this my resignation!

1150
01:21:43,544 --> 01:21:45,065
Effective immediately!

1151
01:21:47,705 --> 01:21:48,665
Soft.

1152
01:21:57,666 --> 01:21:59,106
So, tell me...

1153
01:21:59,546 --> 01:22:02,067
...why do you feel this woman
betrayed you?

1154
01:22:04,348 --> 01:22:05,868
What's the difference?

1155
01:22:05,908 --> 01:22:08,588
The whole world, it seems, is against you?

1156
01:22:08,668 --> 01:22:09,869
I don't know.

1157
01:22:09,989 --> 01:22:11,668
Und the elevator boy...

1158
01:22:11,789 --> 01:22:14,830
...Buzz, he too works against you?

1159
01:22:16,990 --> 01:22:17,990
Classic.

1160
01:22:18,350 --> 01:22:21,471
Patient displayed listlessness, apathy,
gloomy indifference...

1161
01:22:21,551 --> 01:22:23,311
...und was blue und mopey.

1162
01:22:23,791 --> 01:22:27,272
When asked what the Rorschach stains
represented, patient replied:

1163
01:22:27,352 --> 01:22:31,272
"Nothing much. I don't know.
Just a blotch. Sure beats me".

1164
01:22:31,992 --> 01:22:35,113
Patient shows no ambition,
no get-up-and-go, no vim.

1165
01:22:35,793 --> 01:22:37,994
He is riding the grand loopen-ze-loop...

1166
01:22:38,354 --> 01:22:41,194
...that goes from the height
of delusional gaiety...

1167
01:22:41,274 --> 01:22:42,994
...to the trough of despair.

1168
01:22:43,514 --> 01:22:46,195
He is now near,
but not yet at his lowest point.

1169
01:22:46,555 --> 01:22:50,835
When he reaches bottom, he may erupt
und pose a danger to himself...

1170
01:22:51,035 --> 01:22:51,996
...and others.

1171
01:22:52,196 --> 01:22:54,236
Diagnosis, Dr. Bromfenbrenner?

1172
01:22:54,476 --> 01:22:57,355
Patient is eine manic-depressive paranoid,
type B...

1173
01:22:57,516 --> 01:22:59,236
...with acute schizoid tendencies.

1174
01:22:59,596 --> 01:23:01,277
So, patient is...?

1175
01:23:02,877 --> 01:23:03,918
Precisely.

1176
01:23:04,558 --> 01:23:05,558
Nuts!

1177
01:23:05,998 --> 01:23:07,158
Prescription?

1178
01:23:07,358 --> 01:23:09,238
Three things: Commitment...

1179
01:23:09,799 --> 01:23:11,998
...electroconvulsive therapy...

1180
01:23:12,118 --> 01:23:14,479
...maintenance in eine secure facility.

1181
01:23:29,642 --> 01:23:31,762
Yeah, he's a tall guy. A real mess.

1182
01:23:33,482 --> 01:23:36,923
Look, you better get down here.
He says he's a friend of yours.

1183
01:23:37,083 --> 01:23:39,844
He didn't say.
But, man, is he from Squaresville.

1184
01:23:48,125 --> 01:23:49,445
I want a martini!

1185
01:23:50,045 --> 01:23:52,325
It's New Year's Eve. I deserve a martini.

1186
01:23:52,726 --> 01:23:54,446
It's like I've been telling you...

1187
01:23:54,526 --> 01:23:56,606
I thought you served misfits here!

1188
01:23:56,686 --> 01:23:59,126
That's a roger. But we don't sell alcohol.

1189
01:23:59,566 --> 01:24:01,927
What kind of bar doesn't serve martinis?

1190
01:24:02,167 --> 01:24:05,568
It's a juice-and-coffee bar, man,
like I've been telling you.

1191
01:24:05,768 --> 01:24:07,768
Right. So, I want...

1192
01:24:09,088 --> 01:24:10,208
...a martini.

1193
01:24:10,929 --> 01:24:13,889
I've had a martini in every bar
on the way down here.

1194
01:24:14,449 --> 01:24:16,409
Martinis are for squares, man.

1195
01:24:18,330 --> 01:24:21,010
What'd you call me, you beatnik son of a...

1196
01:24:26,892 --> 01:24:28,211
Look who's here:

1197
01:24:28,331 --> 01:24:29,572
Amy Archer...

1198
01:24:29,852 --> 01:24:31,452
...Prizeter Pule winner.

1199
01:24:32,092 --> 01:24:34,252
Looking for a nitwit to buy you lunch?

1200
01:24:35,173 --> 01:24:37,333
-Bar fella, I'd like...
-I'm sorry.

1201
01:24:38,013 --> 01:24:39,374
...a martini, please.

1202
01:24:39,414 --> 01:24:41,735
I tried to tell you so many times, I....

1203
01:24:43,094 --> 01:24:44,494
It's hard to admit...

1204
01:24:44,534 --> 01:24:46,294
...when you've been wrong.

1205
01:24:46,894 --> 01:24:48,295
If you could just...

1206
01:24:48,695 --> 01:24:50,455
...find it in your heart...

1207
01:24:51,055 --> 01:24:52,855
...to give me another chance.

1208
01:24:55,216 --> 01:24:57,576
"You take no prisoners,
give no second chances".

1209
01:24:57,656 --> 01:25:00,416
Please, Norville!
Please give me one more chance!

1210
01:25:01,136 --> 01:25:02,416
And yourself, too!

1211
01:25:02,577 --> 01:25:04,297
We both deserve one.

1212
01:25:04,537 --> 01:25:08,018
Just give us a second chance.
Together we can fight this thing.

1213
01:25:08,178 --> 01:25:12,139
I know the last story was a lie
and we can prove it. Release a statement!

1214
01:25:12,179 --> 01:25:15,059
-I can help you write it!
-What's the difference?

1215
01:25:15,699 --> 01:25:17,019
